 a semester or year since the late 1980s  This was informally arranged until 2001  when formal recognition was established with the UniBw in Hamburg  Both the UniBwH  now HSU  and UniBw M nchen were established in 1973 as institutions of higher learning for young officers in all service branches  Army  Air Force and Navy  who are studying for their Diplom  The three and a half year period of study at the UniBw is usually part of a 12 year commitment to the military  Students attend classes much as they do at other civilian institutions  no uniforms are worn except during military exercises and dress parades  Women have been accepted at HSU since fall 2002  VMI typically sends 2 cadets to HSU in Hamburg for the winter and spring trimesters  January to March and April to June  which correspond approximately to VMI s spring semester  Since 2001  Hamburg has sent two officers  usually lieutenants of about 25 years of age  to VMI for our fall semester  Points of Contact Financial Matters Enrolling in Courses Documentation   Transportation International Programs Col  Sunnen Home Courses Instructional Bundeswehr Exchange Conference Papers Foreign Links VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 